System:
Cooling system with Cool waves

System Description:
The cool waves system comprises of LTG chilled beam with oscillating fans. This system is a compact and ceiling-mounted unit that provides space cooling via convection. Cold water from the campus chilled water loop circulates into the chilled beam. The oscillating fan generates an air current of cool air quietly and uniformly.

The temperature of the cold water supply is dependent on the humidity of the air and dew point temperature. In the case of condensation, there is a condensation trap within the system.

System Parts & Installation Dates:

  • LTG KFA 1000 T/F (1997)
  • TACO 0011-F4 (1997)
